cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.NA, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it presents a method for performing Sparse Principal Component Analysis (SPCA), which is a common technique in multivariate data analysis and machine learning. Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency and performance of the method, which is a common concern in the machine learning community.

The paper may also belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category as it presents a parallel implementation of SPCA using graphics processing units (GPUs), which can process large blocks of data in parallel.

The cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper discusses the optimization formulations of the generalized power method of SPCA, which involves numerical methods for solving optimization problems.

The cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category is a possibility as SPCA is commonly used in image processing and computer vision applications.

Finally, the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category is a possibility as the paper discusses the use of GPUs for parallel processing, which is relevant to the design and control of large-scale systems.
